rComments: Everyone zoned out during his lectures.  What he talked about in lecture barely overlapped with the text.  Didn't give good cues as to what was important. I agree with the other comment that a lot of what he said is oversimplified. Tutorials for this class are a godsend though. Skip lectures but go to the tutorials.

Interesting class and interesting works, however I found Mr. Burgess's lectures to be not so enlightening. I showed up for the first month of lectures or so before realizing I wasn't picking up much from his lessons that I wasn't already getting from the readings. Barely went to lectures after that, got a 75.

He simplified the material too much. He did not pay enough attention to general themes and concepts of the course material and made no effort to connect the different themes in an interesting way. Burgess does not work with the course to fulfil the requirements of a university level course and I am glad I am done with it. Good bye!
